[{"source": "https://www.popsci.com/feed", "title": "Your brain\u2019s \u2018master switchboard\u2019 is an underappreciated marvel", "description": "<figure class=\"Article-thumbnail orgnc-SingleImage orgnc-SingleImage--center orgnc-SingleImage--hasCaption\">\n                    <div class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-wrapper\"><img alt=\"A brain resting on a bed in a cartoon.\" class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-image webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"810\" src=\"https://www.popsci.com/uploads/2023/10/26/Sleeping-brain-hypothalamus.jpg?auto=webp&amp;width=1440&amp;height=810\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"1440\" /></div><figcaption class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-caption\">The brain area called the hypothalamus regulates important behaviors, including sleeping. <span class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-credit\"><a href=\"https://depositphotos.com/photo/human-brain-resting-bed-isolated-white-background-308055344.html\">Depositphotos</a></span></figcaption></figure><p>When you're sleepy or hungry, that's the hypothalamus at work.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.popsci.com/science/hypothalamus-brain-regulation/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Yo", "link": "https://www.popsci.com/science/hypothalamus-brain-regulation", "date_published": "2023-10-26T21:00:00+00:00", "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "Popular Science", "album": "Popular Science", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": "https://www.popsci.com/uploads/2021/04/28/cropped-PSC3.png?auto=webp&width=32&height=32"}, {"source": "https://www.popsci.com/feed", "title": "This electric plane\u2019s 2,000-mile journey is over. Now its Air Force tests begin.", "description": "<figure class=\"Article-thumbnail orgnc-SingleImage orgnc-SingleImage--center orgnc-SingleImage--hasCaption\">\n                    <div class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-wrapper\"><img alt=\"an electric aircraft flying\" class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-image webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"810\" src=\"https://www.popsci.com/uploads/2023/10/26/beta-alia-duke-field.jpg?auto=webp&amp;width=1440&amp;height=810\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"1440\" /></div><figcaption class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-caption\">The aircraft landed at Duke Field in Florida on Oct. 26. <span class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-credit\">Beta Technologies</span></figcaption></figure><p>The Beta Technologies electric aircraft flew from Vermont down to Florida, where the Air Force will check out what it can do. </p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.popsci.com/technology/beta-technologies-aircraft-elgin-air-force-base/\" rel=\"nofollow\">This electric plane&#8217;s 2,000-mile journey is over. Now its Air Force t", "link": "https://www.popsci.com/technology/beta-technologies-aircraft-elgin-air-force-base", "date_published": "2023-10-26T20:30:00+00:00", "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "Popular Science", "album": "Popular Science", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": "https://www.popsci.com/uploads/2021/04/28/cropped-PSC3.png?auto=webp&width=32&height=32"}, {"source": "https://www.popsci.com/feed", "title": "This liquid crystal fabric is \u2018smart\u2019 enough to adapt to the weather", "description": "<figure class=\"Article-thumbnail orgnc-SingleImage orgnc-SingleImage--center orgnc-SingleImage--hasCaption\">\n                    <div class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-wrapper\"><img alt=\"Woman&#039;s hands holding up cloth woven with smart fiber\" class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-image webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"810\" src=\"https://www.popsci.com/uploads/2023/10/26/MIT-ActuatingFibers-01-press.jpg?auto=webp&amp;width=1440&amp;height=810\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"1440\" /></div><figcaption class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-caption\">MIT's FibeRobo could find its way into jackets, sports bras, and compression garments. <span class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-credit\"><a href=\"https://news.mit.edu/2023/shape-shifting-fiber-can-produce-morphing-fabrics-1026\">Courtesy of researchers/MIT</a></span></figcaption></figure><p>Developed by MIT researchers, FibeRobo changes structure with heat and cold.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.popsci.com/technology/fiberobo-smart-t", "link": "https://www.popsci.com/technology/fiberobo-smart-textiles-mit", "date_published": "2023-10-26T20:00:00+00:00", "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "Popular Science", "album": "Popular Science", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": "https://www.popsci.com/uploads/2021/04/28/cropped-PSC3.png?auto=webp&width=32&height=32"}, {"source": "https://www.popsci.com/feed", "title": "Wild chimpanzees show signs of potential menopause\u2014a rarity in the animal kingdom", "description": "<figure class=\"Article-thumbnail orgnc-SingleImage orgnc-SingleImage--center orgnc-SingleImage--hasCaption\">\n                    <div class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-wrapper\"><img alt=\"Ma Rainey, a post-reproductive female of the Ngogo community of chimpanzees in Kibale National Park, Uganda, and her adult son Wes. The two are sitting among trees in a forest.\" class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-image webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"810\" src=\"https://www.popsci.com/uploads/2023/10/26/chimpanzee-menopause.png?auto=webp&amp;width=1440&amp;height=810\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"1440\" /></div><figcaption class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-caption\">Ma Rainey, a post-reproductive female of the Ngogo community of chimpanzees in Kibale National Park, Uganda, and her adult son Wes. <span class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-credit\">Kevin Langergraber/Arizona State University</span></figcaption></figure><p>The evolutionary benefits of living after reproductive age are still debated", "link": "https://www.popsci.com/environment/wild-chimpanzees-menopause", "date_published": "2023-10-26T18:00:00+00:00", "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "Popular Science", "album": "Popular Science", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": "https://www.popsci.com/uploads/2021/04/28/cropped-PSC3.png?auto=webp&width=32&height=32"}, {"source": "https://www.popsci.com/feed", "title": "The best circular saws in 2023, according to experts", "description": "<figure class=\"Article-thumbnail orgnc-SingleImage orgnc-SingleImage--center orgnc-SingleImage--productTable\">\n                    <div class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-wrapper\"><img alt=\"Home photo\" class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-image webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"810\" src=\"https://www.popsci.com/uploads/2023/10/26/best-circular-saws-header.jpg?auto=webp&amp;width=1440&amp;height=810\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"1440\" /></div></figure><p>A solid circular saw will provide years of quick, safe, and straight cuts no matter what project or material you're working on. </p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.popsci.com/gear/best-circular-saws/\" rel=\"nofollow\">The best circular saws in 2023, according to experts</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.popsci.com\" rel=\"nofollow\">Popular Science</a>.</p>", "link": "https://www.popsci.com/gear/best-circular-saws", "date_published": "2023-10-26T17:05:00+00:00", "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "Popular Science", "album": "Popular Science", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": "https://www.popsci.com/uploads/2021/04/28/cropped-PSC3.png?auto=webp&width=32&height=32"}, {"source": "https://www.popsci.com/feed", "title": "The best miter saws for 2023, according to experts", "description": "<figure class=\"Article-thumbnail orgnc-SingleImage orgnc-SingleImage--center orgnc-SingleImage--productTable\">\n                    <div class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-wrapper\"><img alt=\"The best miter saws composited together in four columns with close-up views of each\" class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-image webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"810\" src=\"https://www.popsci.com/uploads/2023/10/26/best-miter-saws-header.jpg?auto=webp&amp;width=1440&amp;height=810\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"1440\" /></div><div class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-creditTop\">Stan Horaczek</div></figure><p>Few tools offer the same power and flexibility as a miter saw, whether you're a DIY enthusiast or a pro contractor.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.popsci.com/gear/best-miter-saws/\" rel=\"nofollow\">The best miter saws for 2023, according to experts</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.popsci.com\" rel=\"nofollow\">Popular Science</a>.</p>", "link": "https://www.popsci.com/gear/best-miter-saws", "date_published": "2023-10-26T17:00:00+00:00", "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "Popular Science", "album": "Popular Science", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": "https://www.popsci.com/uploads/2021/04/28/cropped-PSC3.png?auto=webp&width=32&height=32"}, {"source": "https://www.popsci.com/feed", "title": "FTC smacks down makers of bogus \u2018invisible mask\u2019 against COVID-19", "description": "<figure class=\"Article-thumbnail orgnc-SingleImage orgnc-SingleImage--center orgnc-SingleImage--hasCaption\">\n                    <div class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-wrapper\"><img alt=\"Woman sneezing into tissue on train\" class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-image webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"810\" src=\"https://www.popsci.com/uploads/2023/10/26/Depositphotos_153693126_L.jpg?auto=webp&amp;width=1440&amp;height=810\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"1440\" /></div><figcaption class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-caption\">The '1 Virus Buster Invisible Mask' promised to generate a 3-foot-radius of protection in public spaces. <span class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-credit\"><a href=\"https://depositphotos.com/photo/woman-sneezing-in-train-153693126.html\">Deposit Photos</a></span></figcaption></figure><p>Shockingly, the $29.99 'pouch of ingredients' does not provide a 'protective gaseous barrier' that busts the virus.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.popsci.com/technology/ftc-fake", "link": "https://www.popsci.com/technology/ftc-fake-covid-mask", "date_published": "2023-10-26T16:00:00+00:00", "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "Popular Science", "album": "Popular Science", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": "https://www.popsci.com/uploads/2021/04/28/cropped-PSC3.png?auto=webp&width=32&height=32"}, {"source": "https://www.popsci.com/feed", "title": "Why electric knifefish \u2018shimmy\u2019", "description": "<figure class=\"Article-thumbnail orgnc-SingleImage orgnc-SingleImage--center orgnc-SingleImage--hasCaption\">\n                    <div class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-wrapper\"><img alt=\"A long torpedo-shaped fish swims among green plants. Knifefish like the black ghost knifefish are known for their shimmying motions and electrical pulses. and live in freshwater lakes and rivers in Central and South America.\" class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-image webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"810\" src=\"https://www.popsci.com/uploads/2023/10/26/electric-knifefish-shimmy.png?auto=webp&amp;width=1440&amp;height=810\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"1440\" /></div><figcaption class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-caption\">Knifefish like the black ghost knifefish are known for their shimmying motions and electrical pulses.  and live in freshwater lakes and rivers in Central and South America. <span class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-credit\"><a href=\"https://depositphotos.com/photo/black-ghost-knif", "link": "https://www.popsci.com/environment/electric-knifefish-shimmy", "date_published": "2023-10-26T15:00:00+00:00", "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "Popular Science", "album": "Popular Science", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": "https://www.popsci.com/uploads/2021/04/28/cropped-PSC3.png?auto=webp&width=32&height=32"}, {"source": "https://www.popsci.com/feed", "title": "This sea-to-farm-to-table restaurant wants kelp to catch on", "description": "<figure class=\"Article-thumbnail orgnc-SingleImage orgnc-SingleImage--center orgnc-SingleImage--hasCaption\">\n                    <div class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-wrapper\"><img alt=\"A steak with kelp on top is plated by a chef holding a sauce pan.\" class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-image webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"810\" src=\"https://www.popsci.com/uploads/2023/10/25/steak-kelp.png?auto=webp&amp;width=1440&amp;height=810\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"1440\" /></div><figcaption class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-caption\">Steak and local kelp at The Shipwright\u2019s Daughter, a sustainable farm-to-sea-to-fork restaurant located in historic Mystic, Connecticut. <span class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-credit\">Bread & Beast Photography.</span></figcaption></figure><p>How The Shipwright\u2019s Daughter in Mystic, Connecticut experiments with supply chains and flavor profiles.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.popsci.com/environment/kelp-fine-dining-restaurant/\" rel=\"nofollow\"", "link": "https://www.popsci.com/environment/kelp-fine-dining-restaurant", "date_published": "2023-10-26T14:00:00+00:00", "bookmarked": false, "dead": null, "artist": "Popular Science", "album": "Popular Science", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": "https://www.popsci.com/uploads/2021/04/28/cropped-PSC3.png?auto=webp&width=32&height=32"}, {"source": "https://www.popsci.com/feed", "title": "Holiday travel plans? Save big with Dollar Flight Club, now as little as $40 for life", "description": "<figure class=\"Article-thumbnail orgnc-SingleImage orgnc-SingleImage--center orgnc-SingleImage--hasCaption\">\n                    <div class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-wrapper\"><img alt=\"Travel deals search displayed on an iPhone with a beach background\" class=\"orgnc-SingleImage-image webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"1080\" src=\"https://www.popsci.com/uploads/2023/10/24/image.jp